      "text": "The town was originally called Bellamy Station before adopting the name Waldo, after doctor and politician Benjamin Waldo.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        2,
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Waldo%2C_Florida"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Waldo grew around the Florida Railroad, which reached the town in 1859 and later added a branch to Ocala in 1876.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        8,
